Iavan Pijoos, News24(File, iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - A woman was arrested on Tuesday morning while she was allegedly paying a hitman to kill her husband, Western Cape police said.&nbsp; She was caught during a sting operation while allegedly handing an undisclosed amount of cash to a man in the parking lot of the Lansdowne railway station, Captain FC van Wyk said.&nbsp;Detectives and members of the Manenberg serious and violent crimes investigation unit received information that she was allegedly conspiring to commit murder. The 44-year-old woman from Kenilworth was arrested around 10:00. She was expected to appear in the Wynberg Magistrate's Court on Thursday on a charge of conspiracy to commit murder. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.